Class TempDirectoryUtil

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.matsim.contrib.matrixbasedptrouter.utils.TempDirectoryUtil
  • Deprecated. 
    To get a temporary directory for production, use Files.createTempDirectory(Path, String, FileAttribute[])}. For tests, use the JUnit4 TemporaryFolder Rule.
    (This class is now using nio.file.Files#..., so maybe it is ok to leave it as it is as a wrapper. kai, aug'15)
